-- Saudi Telecom May Buy Infratel, GTL Venture Stake, Business Standard Says
-- Rakteem Katakey
-- 2010-06-29T01:40:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/saudi-telecom-may-buy-infratel-gtl-venture-stake-business-standard-says.html

          
          
             Saudi Telecom Co. may buy a 10
percent to 15 percent stake in the venture created after
Reliance Infratel Ltd., a unit of Reliance Communications Ltd.,
and GTL Infrastructure Ltd. merged this week, Business Standard
reported, citing people it didnâ€™t identify.  
 The deal may be at a premium of as much as 25 percent to
the market value of the venture, according to the newspaper. The
Carlyle Group, Blackstone Group LP and the Abu Dhabi Investment
Corp. are also interested in buying the stake, the newspaper
said.  
